{
  "stem": "17526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Russians were pushing westward and Auschwitz-- Blechhammer was a-- a branch of Auschwitz, it was a satellite of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all the camps, all the surrounding camps around Auschwitz-- which Blechhammer was was one of them-- had to be evacuated towards the west.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was the first big death march that took place, as far as I'm concerned.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "January the 18th, 1945.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Up until then, I was in Blechammer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That much lasted for about a week to 10 days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This just is impossible to describe-- no food and no clothes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We took the blankets that we had that we covered ourselves in camp and we walked, thousands of us-- --on their way through Gross-Rosen, which was another concentration camp, Gross-Rosen.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "From Gross-Rosen, we were shipped by cattle cars to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "From Buchelwald, I was shipped to Speichingen, which is S-P-E-I-C-H-I-N-G-E-N.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And from Speichingen to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Speichingen was a torturous camp, a camp-- a camp just for torture.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There was these lime shafts and we had to dig lime shafts.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And God punished us on top of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a severe winter of '45, this was April '45, and we were just standing there naked and barefoot with-- and deep-- deep shafts.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had to dig out-- there were-- there were these rail cars on top and there were different levels and we had to load lime or-- or-- or-- this was just a tortuous thing.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And from there to Dachau and from Dachau on the way to the Tyrols, there were specific orders by Himmler to be shot, all these inmates.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But fortunately, the American Amy circled and circled these transports and we were liberated on the way somewhere near Garmisch in Bavaria on April 29, 1945.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
